      <head>Richard Bloch (Hupka)</head>

      <div>
        <p>Brother of <ref cRef="entity-000422">Mrs.
        Kaposy</ref> and <ref cRef="entity-000399">Felix Hupka</ref>.</p> 
          
          <p>In 1918, Bloch had Zionist
          literature sent to Schenker. He was evidently a supporter of Zionism, and perhaps changed
          his family name from Hupka to Bloch for idealistic reasons.</p>
      </div>
